Pre-heat the #oven{} to 140 degrees and boil a #kettle{} of water. Put the @bulgur wheat{1%cup} in a #bowl{} and pour over the boiling water. Leave for ~{1%minute}, stir for another ~{30%seconds}, then drain the water. Spread the bulgur wheat on a #baking tray{} and put it in the oven for ~{20%minutes} before removing.

Meanwhile chop the @vine tomatoes{2} and @cucumber{1} into tiny (½ cm if possible) cubes. The easiest way to do this with a cucumber is to slice it in 4 strips lengthways, turn it around then slice lengthways into around 8 strips. Lastly chop widthways into cubes.

> See picture for cucumber chopping technique!

Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{2} and chop ⅔ into roughly 1 cm cubes and the remaining ⅓ into ½ cm cubes (don't mix the two up as we'll use them separately!). Finally, very finely chop the @garlic cloves{2}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on medium-high heat. Once really hot carefully add your @minced beef{500%g} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and brown it off on the outside before removing. If necessary cook it in a couple of batches so you don't overcrowd the pan (which can stew the meat).

Now cook the 1cm cubed yellow pepper in the #frying pan{} (add a little more @olive oil{1%tsp} if you need). Once it's a little coloured on the edges and cooked through add the @ras-el-hanout{1.5%tbsp}, the mince beef and stir everything together for ~{1%minute} before removing.

Coat the @pitta bread{6} on both sides in a little @olive oil{1%tsp}, the garlic and some @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Put them in the oven for ~{5%minutes} until they crisp up a tiny bit then remove.

Toss together the bulgur wheat, cucumber, remaining ½ cm yellow pepper and the tomato with a tbsp of @olive oil{1%tbsp}. If you have any @?parsley{} from your other recipes, chop all of this and add it too. If you happen to have any @?lemon{1}(squeezed), squeeze in a tbsp of juice too.

> If you have other herbs left over in your fridge, you could also add mint or coriander.

> Serve with @?Greek style natural yoghurt{1/2%cup} on the side.

Serve the meat on top of your pitas with the tabbouleh on the side and go for it!